    A FilterSpecifierFactory that accepts three types of inputs: null, which returns ShorthandFilterSpecifier that matches everything inFilterOf(foo), which returns InterfaceSpecifierFilterSpecifier with foo being fed to FlexibleInterfaceSpecifierFactory outFilterOf(foo), as above but for output filters ref.filtergroup(foo, bar), which returns ReferenceFilterGroupFilterSpecifier; inputs accepted by ShorthandFilterSpecifier

    FlexibleInterfaceSpecifierFactory
    A InterfaceSpecifierFactory that accepts three forms of input null: returns ShorthandInterfaceSpecifier(InterfacesSpecifier.ALL) connectedTo(ip, prefix, or wildcard): returns InterfaceWithConnectedIpsSpecifier ref.interfaceGroup(foo, bar), which returns ReferenceInterfaceGroupInterfaceSpecifier; vrf(regex): returns VrfNameRegexInterfaceSpecifier zone(regex): returns ZoneNameRegexInterfaceSpecifier all other inputs go directly to ShorthandInterfaceSpecifier
    FlexibleIpSpaceSpecifierFactory
    An abstract IpSpaceSpecifierFactory that accepts the following types of inputs: null, which returns a default factory provided by the subclass.

    FlexibleNodeSpecifierFactory
